description:
Overview

Metallo, the man with the Kryptonite heart, is being transported by Superboy to a new maximum-security prison until he ends up holding the Boy of Steel's life in his metallic hands in the final issue of the series!Â  Cover by Kevin Maguire and Ty Templeton.

Supported by the mysterious 'Sons of Liberty,' Pete Ross is elected to Congress. Will Superman find out in time to warn his boyhood friend? Meanwhile, Jimmy Olsen and Bibbo try to bring a little holiday cheer to the poor children of Metropolis.

Notes:

  • An ape that resembles Titano and Jimmy Olsen appears as Turtle Boy in a television commercial for Titano's Pizza.
  • With the assassination of Senator Caldwell, Pete Ross receives a call from the governor of Kansas appointing Pete to serve the remainder of the late Senator's term in the Senate.
  • Triangle 1992 #7.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #64.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #674.
name: Christmas in Suicide Slumberland

description: Vixen returns and is stronger than ever! Is Ellen Baker getting a job working in comics?
name: Who is That Masked Woman?

description:
Poseidonis becomes the target of hundreds of sharks that refuse to obey Aquaman. And in nearby Tritonis, Iqula, that city's hero, is introduced.

Aquaman has returned to the his city, where he is greeted by several Atlantean children. However a pack of sharks, smelling the blood in the water from all the previous fighting swim towards Atlantis ignoring Aquaman's suggestions to leave. Aquaman then begins a physical battle with the sharks,meanwhile in the Atlantean city of Tritonnis more shark attacks occur, with an Atlantean being saved by Lord Iqula.

Aquaman is then forced to save the current king when sharks enter the royal palace. Aquaman then realizes he is outnumbered, he begins utilizing his telepathy to call in a school of moses sole, who begin releasing a shark repellent.,while Tritonis prepares to invade Poseidonis,in the name of protecting them.

Aquaman then prepares his final plan to repel the sharks through the use of electricity. Which he manages as Vulko awakens from his head injury he sustained,with damage to his memories. Shortly after driving off the sharks, the armies of Tritonis arrive.
name: The World Around Them
All This, And World War Too!

description:
Batman catches wind of a sinister plot!

Buildings in Gotham are being Imploded. Batman needs to first figure out why these particular buildings are being destroyed before he can figure out which one is next and who is doing it.
name: The Destroyer Part One: A Tale of Two Cities

description: Black Canary must come to terms with her own problems even as she fights to end a drug war and protect Gan from the white supremacists behind it.
name: New Wings Part 4: Just Say "Thank You"

description:
A New Year's Eve gala turns into a nightmare when a failed magician-turned-maniac unleashes his horrible genetic experiments on innocent partygoers. Black Hood is on the scene, but he's unarmed -- and there's a hostage involved! Nate must think on his feet, or a lot of innocent people won't live to see the new year...

The Black Hood will not soon forget this New Year's Eve as his date is kidnapped from the Mayor's party by the vengeful Nate Haskell's "creeptures."
name: Half A Dog

description: The Question, Green Arrow and the Butcher finally all meet up in a small town in Canada investigating the murder of a lumber baron. There are more questions than answers and things get worse when they investigate Arthur Youngblood and find out he is clear cutting miles of forest.
name: [Untitled]

description: A rogue agent of the Web discovers the secret identity of the Comet. What will Rob Connors do? Â
name: Shattered Secrets

description: Kent and Inza Nelson fight to save the Earth from Chaos, as the saga of the Doctor Fate helmet concludes.
name: Currents of Power

description: Cliff, Josh, and Yankee Doodle crash a Brotherhood of Dada political rally. And the Mister Nobody saga comes to a startling conclusion.
name: After the Cabaret
Europe '92, Part 2: The Sounds of Silence

description: "Last Resorts." Flash and friend Mason Trollbridge battle a mysterious villain. Connie's friendship with Chunk strengthens while her relationship with Wally declines. Guest starring Powergirl.
name: Last Resorts

description: Ever wonder what it's like to be imprisoned for someone else's enjoyment? Dolphus gives the Fly and Oceanworld a taste of being a dolphin as he tries to free the park's dolphin inhabitants. Â

Regeneration: Part 2 of 5. "Trials!". The deadly mercenary known as Flicker has ambushed Hal Jordan and plans to make money off his Green Lantern captive. This will bring Hal face-to-face with one of his deadliest adversaries - the Star Sapphire!
name: Trials

description: Constantine is in interview with the King of Vampires who wants John to work for him. But Constantine refuses.
name: Remarkable Lives

name: Breakdowns Part 13: Ex-Factor
Breakdowns Part 14: The Ceremony of Innocence

description: The Shield battles the deadly Weapon (from #4) as the mystery of the original Shield continues to unravel. Â

The Dominators devise another insidious plan, Laurel Gand battles B.I.O.N., and the Legion S.U.B.S. go into action against the Dominators!

B.I.O.N. mistakes the adult Legion for their younger counterparts and attacks them at their headquarters on Talus.
name: Terra Mosaic Part 2

description:
This issue has a lot of questions and few answers.Â  Ray Terrill bumps into his cousin Hank Terrill at his father's funeral.Â  Ray had only just discovered that his father was the superhero known as the Ray and for some reason Hank knows it too and convinces him to see if he has his father's power.
Â 
Ray grew up in literal darkness unable to control his power.Â  Ray has no idea why this is because he was told he had an allergy to light.Â  He also pines for Jenny Jurden a girl he grew up with.Â  She was the love of his life having not met any other girls.Â  She is also very sweet and wasn't scared of Ray and treated him kindly.Â  Now that Ray has control of his powers he goes and sees her but there are others who are watching him including it seems his father whom Ray believes is dead.
name: Grander Than Fire

description:
Barbie finds herself far from home and wandering alone through the Land, finally encountering the enemy she's been waiting for--the Cuckoo. Part 4 of 6.

In this story, Barbie finds herself wandering in the Land, far from home. There, she finally encounters the enemy she's been expecting....the Cuckoo.
name: A Game of You, Part 4: Beginning to See the Light

description: Sgt Rock goes on night patrol alone after a grueling 26 days of fighting with Easy Co. left battered and bloody. During an ambush, the sarge makes a kill that leaves him haunted and thinking "It's a dirty war." The ending? How about this for a no-spoiler: A child shall lead them - astray? Great read. More stories included in the issue, too.

Shade stops at a bar on his way to Montana and runs into a gang of unruly bikers. Must Shade resort to the madness, or should he allow Sadist Shade, his alter ego, to take charge of his identity?

Shade is making his way back to Kathy, but on his journey he stops at a bar where he wishes to just drink and be anonymous but his flamboyant coat gets him in trouble when a biker starts harassing him and calling him "Pretty Boy". This confrontation comes to a head when the biker again attacks him in the bathroom where Shade is busy talking with his "brother", Hades. Shade uses the Madness to distort his face into a beast causing the biker to collapse in believing he has just seen the Devil.

Shade then gives control to Hades and the next thing he knows, it's morning and he's in bed with the girl of the lead biker, he has nail marks in his back and a tattoo on his torso...

Kathy meanwhile remains at her Uncle's house and is excited when Lenny arrives with a stolen car and a cowboy blow-up doll, the two begin to kindle a romance and begin to plan a road trip, only to have Shade return. The meet-up isn't the running into each other's arms that it should have been, and in fact Shade feels more like he's lost Kathy but she does invite him on their road trip and the trio sets out on the road...
name: The Road, Prologue

description: The Shadow, Margo Lane, and Harry Vincet go to Hawaii for rest, refueling and a "single minor errand" in "Aloha."
name: Aloha From Paradise!

description: Part 4 of 4. Kirk protects an entire world from the Romulan threat...and then confronts his betrayer!
name: Truth...Or Treachery

description: On the anniversary of the death of his mate, Worf is drawn into an alien scheme that would return her to life...but at the cost of the Enterprise and its crew.
name: The Remembered One

description: Part 2 of the 4-part 'Star Shadows': Hoping to find a cure for his wildly fluctuating powers, Starman heads into outer space with Dr. Bruce Gordon...where they meet up with Lobo, who's been hired to kill Gordon's alter ego, Eclipso!
name: Star Shadows, Part 2: Blue Moon

description:
Ray Palmer returns to avenge the death of Adam Cray!

The new Atom deals with tiny espionage agents. Who will survive? Well, look at the title.
name: Number the Dead

description: Meet the members of the Posse, the newest - and the youngest - agents of the Web. Â

Christmas even finds Box and Diamond Lil celebrate their respective bachelor and bachelorette parties. Madison's bachelor party is held up by a despareate man which causes the men of Alpha Flight to saveÂ  Christmas for a child.
name: The Bachelor Party

description:
The Avengers take on Swordsman and his mysterious accomplice Magdalene. Swordsman withdraws because of a crippling headache, and Magdalene reveals her dimension-warping abilities!

The Avengers find themselves lured into an ambush by someone claiming to be a long dead Avenger and his mysterious lover. The two escape and return to their master, Proctor, leaving the Avengers with nothing about questions about what they face on the horizon. Meanwhile, an alien starship appears in the solar system, straining Earth's sun with the use of a nearby stargate.
name: Echoes of the Past

description: Cap finds himself in a fight for his life as Jack Oâ Lantern and Blackwing try to kill him for fun! But when the Scourge appears the truth about the Redskullâs death is revealed!
name: Shot in the Dark

description: Captain Britain confronts the mysterious Roma, and discovers a dark secret about Exclaibur in the process!

description: Rancor and her band of evil mutants travel to Earth in search of Wolverine --- who, in the 30th Century, is presumably quite dead!
name: The Return Of Rancor

description: Hulk goes to town on a battalion of SHIELD robots!
name: This Means War

description: A masked man sets a bomb in the Spector Mansion driveway. Arriving home, Marc and Marlene drive over the trigger, blowing up the wing of the mansion that houses all Marc's Moon Knight equipment. Marc runs in, looking for Frenchie, while Marlene calls the fire department. While Marc continues to search, Marlene is attacked by Randall outside. Marc finds Frenchie unconscious and manages to escape with him. Outside, Marc finds Marlene also unconscious, holding the Randall's mask. Meanwhile, Randall returns to Princess Nepthys and the Knights of the Moon. Elsewhere, Punisher is tracking some A.I.M. weapons dealers and learns of the Cult of Khonshu's involvement. Moon Knight questions a snitch about the location of his car, followed by Punisher questioning the same man about the Cult of Khonshu. Moon Knight arrives at the location and is instantly attacked by the Knights of the Moon (much to his surprise). Nepthys and Randall reveal themselves, but before Marc gets any answers, Punisher bursts in.
name: Blood Brothers, Part One: The Family That Slays Together...

description: The Warriors travel to Japan to get some answers to the questions revolving around the Taylor Foundation. Just how far are they willing to go to find out what they need to know? The answer may surprise you. Plus, Vance Astovik's father goes too far!
name: The Breaking Point

description: Quasar found himself in a New Universe, discovering that he no longer had a direct connection to the Quantum-Zone or to Epoch, he only had the power that was in the Bands when he crossed-over. He flew to the Moon and found no Watcher there. He interacted with various inhabitants and found that there was a power source that was the most powerful in that world called the Star Brand, which could have the power to return him home. After finding the Star Brand on a retired Air Force pilot named Jim Hanrahan who had vowed never to use it, Quasar explained his situation and asked for the Brand. Jim not fully trusting a stranger wanted proof of Quasarâs sincerity, so they sat and exchanged stories for most of the evening. Finally, exhausted, Jim offered Quasar the Star Brand. It indeed gave Quasar the boost he needed to return home. When he arrived back at his office he embraced his then girlfriend, Kayla, he accidentally transferred the Star Brand to her, thinking it burnt out in transit, Quasar didnât give it a second thought. Unbeknoenst to Quasar, he kept a small fraction of the power.
name: Brave New Universe

description:
The Silver Surfer is brought head on with the Collection Agency... But they are no match for the infamous Surfer.

The Silver Surfer is now face to face with the Collection Agency. They attack him and he shows them just a taste of his power. But they are prepared for him and have devices capable of leeching his energy. The importance of his mission gives him the strength to overcome this.

Surfer decides to see how much of his energy their devices can handle. This cause a major explosion. The leader of the Collection Agency, Jude, is dead.

Meanwhile, the virus has begun to transform in the young girl host. It consumes the child and heads straight for the Surfer, who does not resist it from infecting him. The remaining members of the Collection Agency allow him to leave without a fight.

On the way to Collector, he witnesses a ghostly apparition of someone he knows to be dead. He concludes this is the virus and it cannot be real. He is then drawn into the creature's mouth.
name: Battlelines
How The Groonk Stole Christmas

description: Part 2 of "The Name of the Rose" of 6
name: The Name of the Rose, Part 2: Three the Hard Way

What If no one was watching the Watcher?

Featuring a collection of wacky alternate universe stories including...

What If Thanos changed Galactus into a human being?

What If Dr. Doom was a pediatrician?

What If Wolverine hibernated?

What If you were the Red Skull?

What If the Punisher was a stern, yet fatherly type?

description: X-Factor reaches its 75th issue, and this double-size edition introduces the new super-villian team, The Nasty Boys. Meanwhile, X-Factor goes before the Senate to defend their very existance. Also: the plans of Ricochet and Mr. Sinister are revealed.
name: The Nasty Boys

description:
X-Force battles the Brotherhood. Sauron draws first blood. Elsewhere, Kane is ambushed by MLF in an extra story called "X-Tenuating Circumstances."

Synopsis

On the ground, Warpath and Siryn stare down Toad of the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, along with Blob and Pyro. In the air, Shatterstar and Sauron tussle. This seems foolish to Sauron, as he is the only one with wings. Shatterstar throws caution to the wind and lashes out with one of his swords. On his way down he adjusts himself to break his fall with a tree branch that he swings deftly from. Seeing Sauron still airborne, Shatterstar runs for the armory for some long range weapons.

With his wealth of knowledge, Masque finds an opening to the secret X-Force base. With him are Phantazia and Thornn, sister of Feral. Having gained the entrance, Masque flips on the lights and the trio walk in to find some very high grade weaponry. They plan to set some explosives, but shots ring out all around them and they turn to see Cable and some members of X-Force waiting to counter any attack. Cable, finally tired of his home being invaded, tells Masque that his time is finally up.

Outside, Warpath is successful at getting the Blob into a ditch. Siryn takes out Pyro with a quick sonic jab to his throat, but Toad springs up and takes her from behind. He exhibits a new power: the ability to excrete a goo from his hands. Attempting to seal Siryn's mouth, Toad actually ends up getting shot in the back by a freshly returned Shatterstar. Siryn is grateful for the help and the three head inside to figure out what is going on.

What's going on is that Thornn hits the lights and a scuffle begins in the dark. Feral immediately attacks her sister while Cable, able to see, tries shooting Phantazia down. Her powers scramble his circuitry, however, and he instead guides Cannonball right into her. Unfortunately for Cannonball, Phantazia's powers can disrupt humans as well and he goes careening off. Cable has had enough playing in the dark and he orders X-Force outside. Feral, however, can't pull herself away from the fight with Thornn. The sisters continue at it. Thornn enjoys being able to take her aggression out, especially after all Feral has put her through. Thornn ultimately wins and leaves Feral lying on the floor.

At the underground entrance, Sauron enters and sees Cannonball flying towards him. Cannonball's powers are still going haywire and they glitch right as Sauron swings a pointed wing at his abdomen. Being temporarily vulnerable, Cannonball is impaled right through the gut. X-Force catches up to see Cannonball hanging from the wing of Sauron. Boom Boom can't believe her eyes. Cannonball is dead.

X-Tenuating Circumstances

Garrison Kane, the latest Weapon X, plants himself outside a warehouse in Canada. He'd been called in to round up some smugglers of liquor and cigarettes. He scans the premises and notes only six warm bodies. On his own signal, Kane busts through the door and effectually kicks the crap out of the inhabitants. He notices that they are uniformed, an oddity for mere smugglers. He gets a smack in the back of the head and falls to the floor. He turns and sees that the six men were not the only inhabitants of the warehouse. Sumo, Forearm, and Wildside of the Mutant Liberation Front greet him, leaving Kane to wonder what he's gotten mixed up in. This story continues in X-Force #9.
name: Under the Knife

description: The fight becomes personal as Logan faces off against old enemies and future threats!
name: Blowback

name: Destroyer Part Two: Solomon

description:
After saving the universe from Thanos and ultimately acquiring his prize, the Infinity Gauntlet, Adam Warlock finds himself on trial, judged by the very cosmic beings who supported him in the conflict.

The Aftermath of the Infinity Gauntlet.

Following the events from the Infinity Gauntlet miniseries, Adam Warlock maintains posession of the six Infinity Gems and has the combined might of a demi-god. This issue deals with the case brought before the Living Tribunal initiated by Eternity wherein he claims that an artificial being like Adam Warlock who has had a brief, but tumultus past, is unfit for weilding the vast power currently in his grasp. After a confrontation, the Living Tribunal agrees with Eternity and Adam Warlock is sentenced to distribute the six Infinity Gems among five other individuals, retaining the Soul Gem for himself, and also the Living Tribunal decrees that the Infinity Gems may never be used in unison again unless Eternity himself wills it. So begins a great cosmic series by writer extraordinare, Jim Starlin.
name: Judgment

Cerebus is flying through storm clouds, he eventually ends up on the "Seventh Sphere." The Cirinists start excuting people while Punisher Roach runs away, that is until he realizes he has an "automatic crossbow" and starts on a Cirinist killing spree, including Swartskof. Mrs Copps and Mr. Hammond discuss the making of the mold for the gold sphere for Cirin's ascension. Elrod appears again and we see Astoria in jail, but being told by a glowing thing that she'll be out soon. On the Moon, the judge and his evil twin are arguing, and the Regency Elves are there too.

description:
Saint Johnny saves Darkhawk from Tombstone and patches him up. Saint Johnny also holds back secrets and acts as if he doesnât know about his arm turning into a ray blaster, or any thing about Chris and Darkhawk. Chris can not switch back. Darkhawk stumbles back home to get some clothing to cover his body up. Darkhawk passes out.

Grace discovers him in the house and he crashes out his bedroom window. Chris as the covered up Darkhawk spends the night at the hospital with the twins.

The trial to convict Bazin continues. His own son takes the stand, black mailed by Allegra, to convict his father of multiple murders. Darkhawk had fallen asleep at the hospital and takes off just in time to encounter Savage Steel crashing through courthouse to kill Bazin. It ends up being Lennox who was taken down faster than the previous times. Bazin makes an escape by chopper as Mike Powell resurfaces and disappears with the chopper.
name: Heart Of The Hawk (Part 3):  Masks

description:
You can read this comic online free at http://www.elfquest.com/gallery/OnlineComics3.html

Winnowill has been reawakened in a future age of the world of two moons, and her lust for control has taken on new forms. She battles and overpower Rayek, Zhantee, and even Leetah. It seems that all hope is lost because Winnowill threatens to claim all of the powers of The High-Ones for hersela, until Venka intervenes. The same symbol, a cross of light, appears over her forehead as when Rayek took the Cosmic Egg out of time in ElfQuest: Kings of the Broken Wheel #3. When the battle ends, Leetah was hurt, but she wakes up and discovered that Cutter was alive the whole time.

Cutter made a deal with Picknose to seal his kinsfolk in the caves, preserved in the endless sleep that Petalwing's wrapstuff provides. Thus, while Rayek has left time from the world of two moons, the Wolfriders escape time by hibernating; all except for Cutter, who is forced to make friends with Old Maggoty and wander the surface of his world in solitude.

Venka has one final confrontation with the zeal of her father Rayek. She tells him that Cutter and the Wolfriders were responsible for her upbringing, expressing that she was abandoned by him just as Cutter expressed this in earlier issues.

volume.name: ElfQuest: Kings of the Broken Wheel

description: The colonial war on Venus begins to turn in favor of the Ishtarian aggressors, who capture the abandoned capital of Aphrodia. As refugees flee from the city, a full Ishtarian armored division turns toward the refugee camp and oxygen plant defended by Ken Seno and the tattered remnants of the Hound Battalion. The Hounds must make a fateful choice: Do they face certain death in order to give the refugees time to escape, or do they live to fight another day and leave the helpless refugees to the not-so-tender mercies of the armies of Ishtar?

description:
Pete discovers a new Harbinger, but does he share their rebellious teen spirit or does he belong in the Harbinger Foundation?

Wishing to decode stolen Harbinger Foundation disks, the kids contact a hacker named Ax. When Pete mind-probes the obnoxious hacker, he unleashes Ax's psionic command of computers. The disks contain information on Spider Alien base sites, which they use to steal an alien spacecraft. Flying it to the alien moonbase, they soon regret making the trip when they are captured by the armored Rexo and his Spider Alien allies.

Contains a coupon for Harbinger # 0 Pink.

1st appearance:

  • Ax
  • Rexo
name: One Small Step...

description:
Afraid of Synchron and as North Am is helpless without power, President Clane decides to take desperate measures and has Xyrkolâs mind freed from the pycho probe in order to get him to help North Am defend itself. But Xyrkol, of course, plays by his own agenda in âThe Xyrkol Trilogy Part Two â Freedomâs End.â

As Magnus is about to be psycho-probed, the Freewills of Synchron retaliate against North Am with a nuclear missile strike. The explosions knock out North Am's power, and Magnus escapes in the confusion. Desperate, President Clane turns to criminal genius Xyrkol for a means to strike back. Instead of helping Clane, Xyrkol uses his new power to subdue Magnus and prepare to conquer chaos-stricken North Am!
name: The Xyrkol Trilogy Part 2: Freedom's End

description:
Meet Takao Konishi, the last Rai! With the Blood of Heroes coursing through his veins, Rai will lead humanity's liberation from the all-knowing, all-powerful sentient nation known as Grandmother. But when you upset Grandmother, you must be punished.

Now that the Grandmother computer no longer rules Japan, the orbiting nation is split between the ruling Humanist party, and the Healers, who want to restore computer control. When the Healers attempt to steal a component from the Skull-dome control center, Rai and Kazuyo find themselves forced to battle a deadly Grandmother drone! But the terrible fight is only a diversion, designed to hide the Healers' true objective.

In this issue we meet Makiko Minashi a man who was raised from birth to be the protector of the people of Japan. He takes the title of Rai. He follows the teachings of Japans master computer called Grandmother. This makes it impossible for him to pick a side in the impending revolution.
name: New Moon Asunder

description: As Solar destroys the Spider Alien fleet near Saturn, an alien warrior hurries to don his Manowar-class X-O Armor. At first unimpressed by this armored soldier, Solar soon learns that even he can succumb to the power of the Manowar! A desperate ploy provides Solar with the energy to beat his enemy, but some of the fleet have escaped to warn their Homeworld of the terrible Earthling they now call the Destroyer!
name: First Strike Part 2: Massacre / Alpha And Omega Part  7

description:
With his friend and ally, Ken Clarkson, Aric brings his war on the Spider Aliens to the heart of their empire on Earth -- the corporate headquarters of Orb Industries. But Lydia and Spider Aliens have set a trap there for their most savage of foes.

Even as Aric and Ken strive to consolidate their new corporate empire, Toyo Harada dispatches the bionic assassin, Sniper, to slay the armored alien seen recently in New York. When Sniper confronts Aric, Harada realizes that this armored warrior is no alien when he shows concern for the injured bystanders! Ordering Sniper to withdraw, Harada ponders how to deal with this powerful new entity.

1st appearance:

- X-O Armor Wolf Class

The issue opens with X-o fighting a spider alien. Afterwards he carries his friend to his home where his doctor roommate stops him from bleeding to death from his severed arm. As they are resting, the house is attacked and Arics friend Eddie ia kidnapped.

He follows his armor to the alien headquarters their he meets and kills what he believes to be the king of the aliens. Only it ends up being a trap set by the queen, yet when she shows her teeth to him, Aric quickly disposes of her.

Ken comes to him after that and realizes that they have just won the war against the aliens.
name: Retribution Part 2: Kingdom Come!

description:
Tommy ascends to the Throne of Odin and uses it to spy on the Oblivion world. Lord Oblivion catches him and obliterates his rocky body. Tommy, without either body now enters a dangerous crossroads. Saker shows up and helps guide Tommy. Releasing him from Monolith, so that it can seek out a new host and then helping Tommy to form a new body for himself. The two of them fly off to meet Lord Oblivion and a deal is struck.

Meanwhile, Vortex learns of the Nacht island invasion by the Oblivion forces. He begins to assemble a reconnaissance crew.
name: Forever in this Halflife

description:
Overview

Stanislaw Mayakovsky and his new "partner" have designed a cyberantic Alien to steal the Alien Queen Mother's royal jelly, the galaxy's most valuable commodity. This issue the cyberantic Alien's big test comes as "Norbert" is sent deep into the heart of an Alien hive.

In chapter 3 of the new Moebius epic, The Man from the Ciguri, the crew of the Ciguri discovers that Major Grubert is missing, and some of the Airtight Garage's inhabitants make a startling discovery about their world. Plus, war games in chapter 5 of Tree-heart, by Comes; black pearls, giant babies, and tiny women in the concluding installment of Jordan, by Makyo and Rossi; and cryptic one-liners in David Lynch's The Angriest Dog in the World! Cheval Noir #28 also features Phil Elliott's Post-Apocalypse and Classics Desecrated: Goldielocks by Douglas Wheeler and Bernie Mireault. This issue's cover painting is by science fiction illustrator Bob Eggleton.

Story Titles

  • The Angriest Dog in the World
  • Jordan Chapter 5
  • Post-Apocalypse
  • The Man From the Ciguri Chapter 3
  • Tree-Heart Chapter 5
  • Classics Desecrated: Goldielocks and the 3 Bears

The action in Frank Miller's Sin City continues at breakneck pace as Marv races toward a confrontation with Goldie's killer. Don't miss this chance to see the master of the comics medium cut loose! In The Creep, Oxel Karnhus, the acromegalic private eye, finally breaks down and buys a gun--and it's a good thing, `cause he's gonna need it! Story by John Arcudi, art by Dale Eaglesham. Finally, the Earth Boys return to Earth, only to find that the planet has changed its name so as not to be associated with the four dangerous youths! Story by Brett Brooks and Cliff Biggers, art by David Johnson. Full color cover by Frank Miller & Lynn Varley.

Chapters

  • Sin City - Episode 11
  • Murder Tour
  • Beautiful Homes
  • The Creep
  • Earth Boys - "Invasion of Privacy"
name: Sin City; Murder Tour & Beautiful Homes; The Creep; Earth Boys

description: Dark Horse Comics proudly presents the first issue of this hard-boiled anthology series consisting of comic-book adaptations of Andrew Vachss' finest short stories. Vachss (Flood, Blue Belle, Sacrifice) is the best-selling author of some of today's best-selling author of some of today's best crime-drama novels. Included in this issue are "Hostage," adapted by writer Neal Barrett, Jr. and illustrated by Gary Gianni, "Unwritten Law," adapted by writer Barbara Kesel and illustrated by Rick Magyar and "Dumping Ground," adapted by writer/artist Dave Gibbons. Also in this issue is "Statute of Limitations," an original, previously unpublished prose piece by author Andrew Vachss and its accompanying illustration by Tim Bradstreet, who also provides this issue's cover.

Overview

In the 21st Century, Skynet and its Terminators are on the brink of defeat at the hands of John Connor. Meanwhile, half a world away in the wreckage of the Soviet Union, a second sentient computer network carries out Skynet's deadly mission; when Skynet falls, its comrades will continue the systematic extermination of mankind. And a new breed of infiltration unit has been created to penetrate the Soviet resistance: Terminators copied from real people. They have the same faces, fingerprints, memories, and personalities of their human counterparts, plus "stealth" circuitry that makes them impossible to detect. They could be anywhere. They could be anyone. And no one will know...until it's too late!

"Panic in the Sky" Part 3! The battle against Brainiac continues on Warworld as Superman, aided by Wonder Woman, Flash, Green Lantern, Deathstroke and others, gains the upper hand. But for how long?

Previously, Superman fought Braniacâs Headship and tossed into the ocean. But it seems that it was not the end. The ship recovered and captured Aquaman, before coming to attack the assembled heroes of the DC universe.

The Headship fires an energy beam at the headquarters of the heroes, disintegrating part of it. This triggers the heroes into attack mode. They have worked out a code language which Brainiac doesnât know. By this way, they hope to conceal future plans of their attack while conversing amongst themselves.

Booster Gold makes an error. He keeps his thoughts unchecked while trying to free the dangling Aquaman. The Headship, which is designed to operate on brainwaves, reads his thoughts and teleports Aquaman inside it. Guy Gardner tries a desperate move. He forms a huge energy fist and slams the Headship into the ground, temporarily disabling it. Dubbilex appears on the Mobius Chair and links his mind with Mr. Miracle to trip the emergency switches inside the ship.

They enter the ship. Dubbilex instructs them to reach the core to free Aquaman. The ship has self-repaired itself from the previous battle with Superman. Guy Gardner has a bad habit of not following orders. He almost comes close to killing Aquaman while trying to generate an energy vice to open the cell door. They free Aquaman after Superman uses his heat vision to fuse the circuits. Miracle says that he will tend to Aquamanâs injuries. Superman says that it is time for them to take the battle to Warworld.

Brainiac and Maxima watch the screens as they near our solar system. Brainiac says that he will carry the fight to Metropolis. He teleports several of Warworldâs fighters to earth. The fighters come down in the streets of Metropolis and are immediately attacked by the remaining heroes. An excellent plan made by Superman thus saves Metropolis from instant annihilation.

Meanwhile, the other heroes are traveling inside Brainiacâs Headship. They make a jump into hyperspace. Dubbilex says that Metropolis has been attacked. After sometime, the ship jumps out of hyperspace in front of Warworld. Brainiac attacks them telepathically but Dubbilex counters him. Brainiac imprisons the ship in a tractor beam and brings it down into the arena.

Superman comes out and finds Draaga waiting for him. He hesitates but surges forward. Maxima and Supergirl are teleported into the arena. The other heroes come out. The battle begins. Draaga and Supergirl do not understand the code language and fall for Supermanâs ploy. The heroes divide into two groups minus Superman and enter Warworld.

Brainiac is furious. He creates an artificial storm. But Superman manages to free Draaga and Supergirl from Brainiacâs influence. He enlists Draagaâs help in fighting Brainiac, with the promise of a duel after that.

  • Chronological continuation from Superman #65.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #675.

description: Buddy and Ellen realize that Maxine is missing! When her triceratops appears wounded, Buddy realizes that something is wrong.
name: The Beat of Darkness

description:
Tritonis attacks Poseidonis as civil war erupts beneath the sea, and Aquaman meets the Mer-men's champion, Iqula. Also introduced is Queequeg, master of technology!

Lord Iqula and his army from Tritonis have finally arrives as Poseidonis intent on conquering in order to protect the city, which they now view as defenseless with the loss of their army and protective dome. Aquaman then rushes off to battle once again when he hears news of the new group of invaders, forsaking Dr. Diade's pleas to recover at the hospital.

Aquaman is shortly captured by the army, but frees himself through his telepathy summoning all manner of sea life to aid him. As Iquala orders the Tritonis army to eliminate the last bit of Atlantis's army who rush to meet their foes, much to Aquaman's horror. Aquaman then begins his battle with Iqula himself,defeating him.

Meanwhile at United Nations, they continue to discuss who shall become the ambassador for Poseidonis, with Aquaman being chosen due to his ability to survive outside of the ocean. Which gives much pleasure to a member, who seeks the muscle to eliminate him. As the remaining citizens of Poseidonis retreat to the old city, without only Vulko and Dr.Driade remaining behind.

Aquaman then leaves to head towards the United Nations, alongside Porm. However on the way he is attacked by QueeQueg who seeks to eliminate Aquaman.
name: Tails & Legs

description: Â The Ventriloquist was released from prison on a technicality. The Street Demonz had taken Scarface's territory and gang. Gordon introduced Batman to his new assistant, Rene Montoya. Batman saw Bruce Wayne's girlfriend, Vicki Vale, kissing her partner.
name: The Return of Scarface, Part One: Mustache Pete is Dead!

description: In an effort to perfect a new genetic drug, Dr. Mel Harvey has become Ozone, an environmental menace. He now presents a major threat to Seaside City, and the only one able to stop him is the Black Hood. Part 1 of 2, continued next issue. Â

description: The Question and the Butcher chase down a lumber truck that tried to kill them and succeed in killing them instead. Meanwhile, Ollie works on finding who sent the funeral wreath to Owen Hester the night he died. Later that night Byron Running Deer gets the town to rise up and to take up arms.

description: A tale of the original Doctor Fate! A special flashback finds Doctor Fate hurled back to the turn of the century where he meets a scientist who may derail Kent Nelson's destiny as Doctor Fate.
name: The Spirit Motor

description:
We meet a Doom Patrol that might have been if two guys named Stan and Jack had chronicled their adventures 25 years ago.

This entire issue is a dream sequence by Danny the Street, who goes on to dream if the original Doom Patrol saved the world from Celestius the Man-God and his sidekick The Living Guru. Both an obvious parody to Galactus and Silver Surfer.

General Notes

Mark Millar would expand upon this parody-universe briefly in one of the four stories contained in The Books of Magic Annual #3.
